27/03/2003
STRUMICA, Macedonia -- At a meeting in Strumica on Wednesday (26 March), Interior Minister Hari Kostov and his Bulgarian counterpart, Georgi Petkanov, discussed the need to step up co-operation. 
The ministers cited organised crime, drug and human trafficking and the threat of terrorist attacks as the major problems facing border control and security forces. 
That same day, police seized 2 kg of heroin, stashed aboard a bus at the Delcevo crossing on the Macedonian-Bulgarian border. 
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 26/03/03)
